Here is the abstract in bullet points:
The paper addresses the urgent issue of global climate change.
It explores the main causes of climate change.
It highlights the wide-reaching effects of climate change on ecosystems, economies, and communities.
It discusses potential solutions to mitigate climate change.
To reduce the impact of climate change and work toward a sustainable future.
\"the most significant %1$s of our time\" → \"the most significant %2$s of our time\".
\"the %1$s in greenhouse gases\" → \"the %2$s in greenhouse gases\".
\"Increasing\" should be \"increase\" to refer to a noun (the rise in greenhouse gases).
\"This warming is linked %1$s…\" → \"This warming is linked %2$s…\"
Here are the grammatical mistakes in the text:
The paper offers an overview of the key factors driving climate change, its effects, and potential solutions.
Increasing greenhouse gases (GHG) cause climate change.
Climate change leads to extreme weather events.
Use renewable energy sources such as solar and wind.
Climate change requires urgent and collective action. By targeting root causes and implementing solutions, its impact can be mitigated.
L\'augmentation des gaz à effet de serre (GES) cause le changement climatique.
La déforestation diminue l\'absorption de CO₂.
Le changement climatique entraîne des événements météorologiques extrêmes.
Utiliser des énergies renouvelables comme le solaire et l\'éolien.
